 Charming Nollywood actress, Chinedu Bernard, has been confirmed dead at the East Side hospital, Enugu. The popular actress was said to have slumped while cleaning the Chapel of St. Leo the Great Catholic Church Federal Housing. The Priest, Rev. Fr. Uchendu Chukwuma, and some parishioners were said to have rushed her to the hospital where she was declared dead. A post made by one of the parishioners read that efforts were being made to contact her family members before depositing her body in the morgue. Choco, as she is popularly known, had featured in many movies, including ‘The Big Mama’s Stick,’ ‘Money fever,’ ‘The Mad,’ ‘The Last Manhood,’ ‘Mad Love’ etc. 